M. CLAUDIUS MARCELLUS, a friend of Cicero, was consul in no. 51, with Servius Sulpicius for his colleague. Cicero tells us that Marcellus had been Curule Aedile in the same year as P. Clodius, Rc. 563 and that he aided Milo on his trial for the murder of P. Clodius. C. viii. 53) calls it, the Lex of Pompeius and Crassus.

M. Marcellus (13.6. 51) failed in his attempt to deprive Caesar of his provinces.
